

Statement of Prior Art for OpenSkiAI

Title:
OpenSkiAI: Open-Source AI for Personalized Sports Coaching and AI Training

Author:
Jamison Young

Date: Thursday January 23rd 2025


Reference:
For more details, visit openski.xyz

Description of the Concept

OpenSkiAI is an open-source concept designed to use artificial intelligence to provide real-time, personalized feedback on athletic performance, initially focusing on skiing. By analyzing video footage, sensor data, or other motion capture methods, OpenSkiAI offers athletes actionable advice to improve their technique.

In addition to its application in sports, OpenSkiAI also serves as a tool for training and retraining artificial intelligence systems. By leveraging motion data, OpenSkiAI can contribute to advancing AI models designed to interpret, evaluate, and replicate biomechanical movements, benefiting broader fields such as robotics, health sciences, and machine learning research.

This system is versatile and can be applied to skiing and other sports requiring movement analysis, such as snowboarding, tennis, swimming, gymnastics, golf, and more.

Technical Foundation
	1.	AI-Based Movement Analysis:
OpenSkiAI employs machine learning algorithms trained on video footage or sensor data to:
	•	Identify biomechanical patterns of motion.
	•	Compare user performance against professional or predefined benchmarks.
	•	Provide real-time or post-session feedback tailored to the user’s needs.
	2.	Customizable Training Models:
	•	The system allows instructors, athletes, or developers to configure AI models based on specific goals, such as improving speed, precision, or efficiency.
	•	Users can integrate the system into tailored workflows for sport-specific coaching or AI training.
	3.	Broader Applications for AI Development:
OpenSkiAI can also be used as a training dataset generator and retraining tool for AI systems that require understanding human or biomechanical movements. This opens possibilities for robotics, healthcare (e.g., gait analysis or rehabilitation), and machine learning research focused on motion prediction or recognition.
	4.	Open Ecosystem for Collaboration:
OpenSkiAI encourages community-driven innovation by enabling developers, instructors, and researchers to contribute and share improvements freely.

Public Intent

The OpenSkiAI project is dedicated to the public domain to ensure accessibility and openness. This concept is not patentable and must remain free for anyone to use, modify, or commercialize without restrictions. However, no party may restrict others from using the idea or its derivatives.

Dedication to the Public Domain

This concept is released under the Creative Commons Zero (CC0) license. By placing it in the public domain, I waive all copyright and related rights in this work to the fullest extent allowed by law. No permission is required to use, copy, modify, or distribute OpenSkiAI.

Patent Non-Assertion Clause

By using, adapting, or commercializing this concept, you agree not to file or assert any patents that would limit others from using, modifying, or distributing this idea or its derivatives. This ensures that the concept remains freely accessible for all.

Publication and Prior Art Statement

This document serves as a public record of the creation and dedication of the OpenSkiAI concept. It establishes prior art under intellectual property laws, demonstrating that this idea existed as of the date of this publication.

For reference and ongoing updates, please visit openski.xyz.

Purpose and Vision

OpenSkiAI aims to democratize access to AI-driven tools, removing barriers to high-quality sports training and AI development. By fostering innovation and collaboration, OpenSkiAI redefines how sports coaching and artificial intelligence can evolve together as a public good.

